22:52.625 --> 22:55.027
How would you analyze the progress of the war while 
you were there? There was no progress.

22:59.411 --> 23:00.392
When I got there, All I saw when I got there, the 
progress to me was the building up of Quang Tri.

23:07.374 --> 23:13.683
When I entered Vietnam, I was stationed with the 
3rd Marine Division, and they just moved up. They

23:15.145 --> 23:16.688
were first, I think, in Dong Ha. I wasn't there yet. 
Dong Ha is a little farther north than Quang Tri.

23:21.114 --> 23:24.359
And they were from the other side of the DMZ. They 
could rocket to Dong Ha. So it's It was a little too

23:27.035 --> 23:32.483
close to the north, so I think they wanted to build a 
base a little farther south where rockets won't

23:27.035 --> 23:32.483
hit it. Dong Ha base was still there, but they moved 
down to Quang Tri. When I got there, they were just

23:36.749 --> 23:39.313
starting to build Quang Tri up. We went from tents 
to – now, this army wasn't there yet, so we were

23:40.796 --> 23:49.709
stealing plywood and things from the Seabees or 
whatever we need stuff from. So we built – within

23:49.729 --> 23:53.194
the first year, we had wooden tents – you know, the 
