26:02.850 --> 26:08.137
one. When you call in fire support, We call in fire 
support by calling our rear or having a frequency

26:10.503 --> 26:16.032
to go to. And our frequency is mostly a 105 howitzer 
or a 155 howitzer. And that's what mostly we got

26:21.060 --> 26:22.903
sometimes. And when you call it in, they check your 
coordinates to make sure they're not in a friendly

26:23.324 --> 26:28.473
area. Then they'll ask for smoke. And they'll send 
one round. And sometimes you're hit so hard, you

26:34.417 --> 26:37.661
say, forget the smoke. Just come in with it, 
because we're really being hit. And sometimes

26:40.465 --> 26:41.346
they do. But sometimes it's like a grab bag. You're 
knowing you're going to get 105s or 155s, but you

26:45.291 --> 26:48.775
don't know what else you're going to get. We were 
out. And this was about 6.30 in the evening, just

26:51.919 --> 26:55.083
starting dust. We can see them moving around. We 
were near a rice pad. what they call scrub brush.

27:01.578 --> 27:03.122
There's a lot of this stuff around. We can see there 
must have been about 30 or 40 of them out there. At

27:05.346 --> 27:08.473
least for us it felt like 5,000, but there's only a 
few. They looked like they were trying to surround

27:10.197 --> 27:14.506
us, but we wanted to hit them, so we called in for 
support. What we were hoping for was a jet or a

27:15.167 --> 27:18.715
helicopter to come in because They're easier to 
work with because they're right there on top of

27:19.015 --> 27:21.998
you. But you get mostly 105s and 155s. So we called 
in, and the guy on the radio was calling in our

27:27.223 --> 27:32.207
coordinates. And he said he kept hollering at this 
guy. And we said, what do you got? He says, I can't

27:36.932 --> 27:41.916
