27:41.976 --> 27:44.539
mic. May I have this? He was talking so far away from

27:46.184 --> 27:53.895
the mic. We couldn't understand what he meant by 
that. This guy said, just give me your

27:56.799 --> 28:00.504
coordinates. We gave him the coordinates, and he 
said, I'm going to drop smoke. I will wait, and then

28:04.409 --> 28:07.473
tell me if you want to fire for effect. That must 
have been, oh, a few minutes later. We looked up,

28:13.572 --> 28:16.997
and in my mind I said, where's the train? Because it 
sounded like a locomotive coming over. And all of a

28:20.402 --> 28:23.688
sudden, the whole ground just shook. And he said, 
fire! And the guy on the bus just thought he meant

28:28.555 --> 28:31.900
fire for effect. And he put three shells. It was New 
Jersey. He put three shells. All we were doing was

28:37.906 --> 28:39.367
ruining it. We thought the world came to an end. I 
did not know shells get that big. We got about, oh,

28:45.113 --> 28:53.682
we must have ran, it felt like for days, but I mean, 
we ran for a couple hundred yards, laid back, and we

28:45.113 --> 28:53.682
said, God, we don't want that anymore. They should 
have said, we're the New Jersey. Please be a bit

28:56.504 --> 28:57.806
advised. You're going to get a train coming over 
your head, and we're going to blow up an entire grid

28:57.826 --> 29:01.990
coordinate for you. That was the only time, and I 
think after that we got real gunshot, but I never

29:01.970 --> 29:09.099
called anything in because we were afraid we'd get 
to New Jersey again. God, I mean, that is the most

29:09.360 --> 29:13.645
powerful shot we have ever, I've ever had. He was on 
me in New Jersey. Thank you for letting me shit in my

29:15.808 --> 29:22.096
pants.

